{"word":"Βαρθολομαῖος","slug":"Βαρθολομαῖος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Βαρϑολομαῖος, ου, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Aram.\">Aram.</a> ‘son of Tolmai’] <b><i>Bartholomew</i></b> one of the twelve apostles <b><a href='B:470 10:3'>Mt 10:3</a>; <a href='B:480 3:18'>Mk 3:18</a>; <a href='B:490 6:14'>Lk 6:14</a>; <a href='B:510 1:13'>Ac 1:13</a>.</b> Some attempts have been made to identify him with Nathanael, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ s.\">s.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:Ναθαναήλ\">Ναθαναήλ</a></el>. <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:βαρέως\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:Βαριησοῦς\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}